<body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong>
        <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %>
    </p>

    <p>
        At <strong>Travella</strong>, we respect your privacy. This policy explains what information we collect, how we
        use it, and how we protect it.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Email address and password (for account creation)</li>
        <li>User profile data (name, color tag, family association)</li>
        <li>Travel history (countries visited per user)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use your information to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Let you and your family log in and manage travel records</li>
        <li>Display shared dashboards for your family</li>
        <li>Improve our services and user experience</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Storage & Security</h2>
    <p>
        All data is stored securely in our database. Passwords are encrypted using industry-standard hashing (bcrypt).
        We do not store plain-text passwords.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your data with third parties. Only your family members can see
        your travel history within the app.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Google Login</h2>
    <p>
        If you use Google OAuth to sign in, we only access basic account details necessary for authentication. We do not
        access your contacts or emails.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You can request account deletion</li>
        <li>You can update your profile information</li>
        <li>We do not collect or store unnecessary data</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
        For questions or concerns, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@travella.com">support@travella.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p>Thank you for trusting Travella with your family’s memories.</p>
</body>

